    <note>Lu(5) Zai [1288] During the Shaoxing period, Zai apparently abandoned his official career and began to build a private library. Dian's [8098] son, Gui's [7049] grandson, Zhi's [1284] brother, Bi's [7051] and Zhuan's [7297] nephew, You's [3640] father. You was Huaidong tiju in 1181 and was also once Jiangxi tiju. You's lineage uncle (zushu), Ju [3633], moved his family (jia) branch of the lineage from Shanyin xian to Yuyao xian. Jiangxi TZ, 10.20b; Lu You, WJ, 23.1b; SHY:ZG, 69.22b-23a; 72.29a. CBD, 3, 2651.</note>
